This paper proposes a new neural network layer structure for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) that employs multilinear projection as the primary feature extractor. The focus is on improving efficiency in CNNs by reducing memory footprint and computation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
